---
import BaseLayout from "@layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About the Headquarters Dojo"
  description="Introducing the Seishinkai Headquarters, the Seishinkan Okubo Dojo. Located in Sakaedori, Shiroishi-ku, this permanent dojo has a total floor area of 200 tsubo, making it the largest of its kind in Hokkaido. Learn about its history and access information."
  lang="en"
  path="/en/dojo/hq/"
>
  <section class="dojo-list">
    <div class="page-container">
      <div class="section__title-area">
        <span class="section-label">HEADQUARTERS</span>
        <h1 class="section-title">Headquarters: Seishinkan Okubo Dojo</h1>
      </div>

      <p class="detail-page__lead">
        [A karate dojo facing Tohoku-dori, on the border between Shiroishi-ku and Toyohira-ku]<br />
        The Headquarters Dojo got its start in March 1986 (Showa 61), when a permanent dojo was established in Shiroishi-ku.<br />
        Continuing karate activities for half a century since the days of the former Sapporo Branch, it is one of Sapporo's most established karate dojos.<br />
        It moved to its current location in 2012 (Heisei 24); with a parking lot and a total floor area of 200 tsubo across the main and annex buildings, it is the largest permanent dojo in Hokkaido.<br />
        Members range from 3 to 84 years old, all enjoying a good workout together. The Headquarters Dojo offers a Junior Class for elementary and junior high school students (Mon/Wed), a General Division for high school students and up (Wed/Sat), a Kids Class for preschoolers and early elementary students (Thu), a Women's Class (Fri), a Junior & Parent-Child Class (Sat), a daytime class for housewives and seniors (Mon/Wed), and an Iaido Division (Sun).<br />
        ※We have also newly established a special class for students who are not attending school.
      </p>
      <p class="detail-page__note">
        ※For details on the days and times of each class, please see the <a href="/en/dojo/shiroishi/">List of Karate Classes in Shiroishi-ku</a>.
      </p>

      <div class="detail-gallery">
        <figure>
          <img
            src="/assets/images/legacy/dojo/hq/Image1.jpg"
            alt="Junior Class practice at the Headquarters Dojo"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <figcaption>Junior Class practice session</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure>
          <img
            src="/assets/images/legacy/dojo/hq/Image2.jpg"
            alt="Parent-Child Class practice at the Headquarters Dojo"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <figcaption>Parent-Child Class practice session</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure>
          <img
            src="/assets/images/legacy/dojo/hq/img6.jpg"
            alt="General Division practice at the Headquarters Dojo"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <figcaption>General Division practice session</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure>
          <img
            src="/assets/images/legacy/dojo/hq/Image3.jpg"
            alt="A class during a one-on-one trial lesson"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <figcaption>Trial lessons available</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure>
          <img
            src="/assets/images/legacy/dojo/hq/img5.jpg"
            alt="General Division practice at the Headquarters Dojo"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <figcaption>General Division practice session</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure>
          <img
            src="/assets/images/legacy/dojo/hq/4.jpg"
            alt="Senior Class and Housewives' Class practice"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <figcaption>Senior Class and Housewives' Class practice</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>

      <h2 class="detail-page__heading">History</h2>
      <div class="detail-gallery">
        <figure>
          <img
            src="/assets/images/legacy/dojo/hq/Image7.jpg"
            alt="The first permanent Headquarters Dojo, 1986 (Showa 61)"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <figcaption>
            ▲1986 (Showa 61): The first permanent Headquarters Dojo, 16 tsubo<br />1-5 Chuo, Shiroishi-ku
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure>
          <img
            src="/assets/images/legacy/dojo/hq/MVC-466X.jpg"
            alt="The dojo after Headquarters relocated in 2002 (Heisei 14)"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <figcaption>▲2002 (Heisei 14): Headquarters relocated - 30 tsubo<br />6-5 Higashi-Sapporo, Shiroishi-ku</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure>
          <img
            src="/assets/images/legacy/dojo/hq/DSC_0005.jpg"
            alt="The dojo after Headquarters relocated in 2005 (Heisei 17) (now the Seishinkan Shiroishi Dojo)"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <figcaption>
            ▲2005 (Heisei 17): Headquarters relocated - 36 tsubo<br />1-4 Chuo, Shiroishi-ku<br
            />Now in operation as the Seishinkan Shiroishi Dojo
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure>
          <img
            src="/assets/images/about/honbu.jpg"
            alt="Full view of the Headquarters Dojo"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <figcaption>▲2012 (Heisei 24): Headquarters established at its current site - 200 tsubo</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>

      <h2 class="detail-page__heading">Access</h2>
      <p>
        <a
          href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/〒003-0021+北海道札幌市白石区栄通２丁目１−２７/@43.0409785,141.3938016,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m5!3m4!1s0x5f0b2bb4690b9e5f:0x622b301003410409!8m2!3d43.0409785!4d141.3959903"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener"
          >2-1-27 Sakaedori, Shiroishi-ku, Sapporo (along Tohoku-dori)</a
        ><br />
        Dedicated parking available - main building 100 tatami mats, annex 60 tatami mats<br />
        About 9 min (750m) on foot from Shiroishi Subway Station, about 18 min (1.4km) on foot from Tsukisamu-chuo Subway Station<br />
        About 4 min on foot from the Chuo Bus "Sakaedori 1-chome" stop
      </p>
      <p class="detail-page__note">
        The parking lot is behind the Headquarters Dojo, behind the annex building (at the very back). During the winter, due to snow, vehicles are parked close together.<br />
        <a href="/assets/pdf/p.pdf" target="_blank">How to Park During Winter (PDF)</a
        >　<a href="/assets/pdf/p4-11.pdf" target="_blank"
          >How to Park April-November (PDF)</a
        >
      </p>

      <p class="detail-page__back">
        <a href="/en/dojo/">← Back to the Dojo & Class List</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
